matched_top_1_cdm_definition: An alphanumeric identifier assigned to a specific patient.
The assemblage of physical properties or qualities by which male is distinguished from female; the physical difference between male and female; the distinguishing peculiarity of male or female.
The number of education years that a subject has competed.
The year in which a person was born.
A geographic ancestral origin category that is assigned to a population group based mainly on physical characteristics that are thought to be distinct and inherent.
Medical history of symptoms, physical examination results, and/or laboratory test results related to mental health.
Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Total of (Frequency Sub-total) x (Severity Sub-total).
